## Task

Update the Motion Studio Pro slide/scene theme so every rendered scene (title, statement, agenda, etc.) adopts the NorCal SBDC design system below. Change the **rendered output** (scene canvas, exported video frames) first; restyle the studio UI chrome only if time allows — the deliverable is the slides.

Ground truth is the "FAV NorCal SBDC Design System" project. If it is bound/attached, read its `readme.md` and `tokens/` for full detail; otherwise the values below are copied verbatim from it and are sufficient.

## Fonts

Load Adobe Typekit kit once per page:
`<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://use.typekit.net/pkl5rjs.css">`

- Display/serif: `"proxima-sera", Georgia, serif` — weight 400 only, letter-spacing `-.05em`, line-height `.93` (as tight as `.82` for hero-scale).
- Everything else: `"proxima-nova", Arial, sans-serif` — mid weights 650/700/800.
- Kickers/labels ("STOCKTON · JUL 7"): proxima-nova, ~11px equivalent, weight 800, uppercase, letter-spacing `.13em`.
- Do NOT self-host the font files (Adobe EULA); the kit link is the only legal delivery.
- The existing Sans/Serif heading toggle maps to nova/sera respectively.

## Color tokens (use as CSS custom properties)

```css
--navy:#0f1c2d; --navy-soft:#253247; --cobalt:#1b5faf; --cobalt-dark:#144b8c;
--pool:#8fc5d9; --pool-pale:#dcecf2; --paper:#fdfdfd; --cream:#f5f1e8;
--slate:#2c3240; --slate-light:#687080; --berry:#c23c3c; --evergreen:#00675c;
--line:#0f1c2d29; --sky-tint:#b9e5f5;
```

Scene color schemes (replace the current swatch list):
1. **Navy** — bg `--navy`, text `#fdfdfd`, kicker `--pool`.
2. **Paper** — bg `--paper`, text `--navy`, kicker `--cobalt`.
3. **Cream** — bg `--cream`, text `--navy`, kicker `--cobalt`.
4. **Cobalt** — bg `--cobalt`, text `#fdfdfd`, kicker `--pool-pale`.
5. **Pool pale** — bg `--pool-pale`, text `--navy`, kicker `--cobalt`.

Berry `#c23c3c` is an **accent only** — never a background or button fill. Use it as a short thick rule (4–5px, ~56–72px wide) under titles or above kickers. Drop any pure-red or off-palette schemes.

## Photo treatment

- Background images/video: `filter:saturate(.86) contrast(1.03)`; grayscale is an acceptable variant for portraits.
- Overlay/protection: navy gradients, not black — e.g. bottom scrim `linear-gradient(180deg, transparent 35%, rgba(15,28,45,.82))`; full scrim `rgba(15,28,45, strength)`. Wire the existing Overlay Strength slider to the navy alpha.
- "Brand" overlay option = flat navy at ~60% + pool kicker text.

## Spatial rules

- Nearly square corners: scene canvas and any chips/buttons 4–6px radius max. No pills.
- Generous margins: keep text inside an inner safe area of ~8% per side; lower-third layouts sit on a left-aligned column, not edge-to-edge.
- Text blocks: kicker (small caps, tracked) → optional 4px berry rule → serif or sans display line → subtitle in nova 650. Left-align by default; center only for single-statement scenes.
- Hairline dividers where needed: `1px solid #0f1c2d29`. No drop shadows on text panels; use flat navy fills instead.

## Motion

- Restrained: entrances use `cubic-bezier(.2,.75,.25,1)` slide-up + settle; photo/mask reveals via clip-path; NO bounces, no springs. Keep existing animation names (Rise, Typewriter, Mask Reveal…) but retime to this easing.
- UI-level transitions .18s.

## Tone (default copy in templates/placeholders)

Plain, direct, second-person, no emoji, no exclamation marks. Sentence case for titles ("Turn your idea into a business"), ALL-CAPS only for kickers.

## Don'ts

- No icons/emoji anywhere in scenes — the brand has no icon set; use typographic labels and numbers.
- No gradients except navy photo scrims.
- No rounded pills, no colored left-border cards, no black overlays.
